commit.message: Check custom alphabet for length and unique characters
Pull salt, min_length and alphabet out of overriding hashids instance for future reduction
Also cache the hashids object in the descriptor
Fix invalid call to Hashid constructor

Cache the hashids object.

Creating the Hashids and then encoding the id
every time appears to take 3x more time than
having the Hashids object cached and ready to
encode a new id.

Fixed int lookup issue with comparison operators. Bump version 3.1.1. Fixes #38
Bump dependency versions.
Fix tests to not rely on other tests changing allow_int_lookup setting.
Add support for comparison operators, add tests for passthrough lookups. Fixes #38.
Cleaned up old backwards-compatible lookup code
Update test suites to test 1.11 on 3.6, 3.7 only
update readme setup, and test matrix
Always use xenial for all travis tests
